HEADWORD: Anchor-hold
<hw>An"chor-hold`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The hold or grip of an anchor, or that to which it holds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence: Firm hold: security.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anchorite</ent>⟦br⟧
